h3. Issue Summary

As documented in the page "[Create a Business Project as a User|https://support.atlassian.com/jira-work-management/docs/create-a-business-project-as-a-user/]":
{quote}
Users can create company-managed business projects if their instance has only a Standard license of Jira Work Management provisioned. This permission can be revoked or granted to user groups by Jira admins and site admins. If an instance has another Jira Cloud product provisioned, e.g. Jira Software, this permission setting will not be available.
{quote}


It would be extremely useful to have this feature also available il sites/instances having also other Cloud product licenses.

h3. Summary

In form, it shows only some specific fields. As a user, I'd like to be able to support all fields. Because some fields are unsupported, if any of them are mandatory you will get the following error:
{panel}
*This form contains unsupported required fields*, which will prevent respondents to submit critical information. Please [contact your administrator|https://featureflagjunkie.atlassian.net/secure/ContactAdministrators!default.jspa] to make these fields optional.{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Cloud*. Using *JIRA Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-63695].
  {panel}

Swimlanes (and the attached JQL schemes) would be very useful in a business context, i.e: creating team to-do lists, creating multi-team projects, etc), but it seems as if this feature was not ported over.

Can we pretty please add swimlanes into JIRA Core? :D
